gura: struggling to count to 12

me: counting the letters I read as I read them from a novel on chapter 756,
14,356th letter for the chapter, 12,657,435th letter for the book.




let me tell you a story, it all started when I was 7, I lived in a military family, we moved a lot, due to this I happened to avoid every single spelling test in school by either good or bad luck, due to this I hated spelling and especially poetry as it added another layer of "unnecessary" complexity. one day when I was tasked with writing poetry I decided rhymes sounded fun. so naturally as a f*cking strange child does, I started thinking for a rhyme for every word before I said it. two years later when it hadn't gotten any easier I discovered I was trash at poetry, free style rap, rap in general, and rhymes in general (better than most at this point but I should've been better after my strange obsession), realizing I had no talent and discovering how oddly good my memory was with numbers, I decided I would start reading things in pairs, first it was paragraphs, next it was lines on a page, next it was sentences, next it was words, I started obsessing over whether or not a page or a book overall was "even" or not. then puberty hit, I hated symmetry(as a lazy teenager I hated order and confinement), and I hated asymmetry(literally have OCD), so I began to hate all forms of pairing words and decided I would simply go to counting. after realizing that words were uneven(aosdfjaowihefoahwefoahw still somehow triggered by that to this day.) I decided I would count letters. so I count letters now. after many years of doing so and thousands of books before finally moving on to novels online since I had read the best of the English language offline and didn't mind a few typos, I kept counting until even I realized it was getting a bit weird and it was getting a little uncomfortable to read and listen to music while counting letters at the same time, so I tried to stop. I failed. I can never stop counting now.

now the only thing I can do is accept it, knowing that I now find myself wandering "if I don't count numbers as letters, should I count numbers in word form as letters? should I count the full word when its abbreviated? should I count some symbols but not others? should I count grunts and exclamations? should I count typos or the original word? what if the word is completely wrong?"

of course this isn't the only weird thing about me, but I find myself genuinely confused at her counting here and had to mention all that so people knew where I stood on the subject, I suppose what I'm really asking is if it's common to be that bad at counting, or is she just a special case?

Gura, streaming everyday while making it fun intentionally and only talking to yourself will wear you out for sure, I have a few suggestions if you want, prepare for a long one.:_GuraAA:

>>You can always check out how other hololive's stream looks like, for example a game stream like Undertale, Outlast, Paper Pls, they don't really need to do any chit chat because its already has non-stop content that keeps coming itself, so you can totally find more games like this to play if you are interested in it. 

>>For streams like minecraft, what I usually see is that they are actually "disguised" as Minecraft stream but in truth they are chatting stream, unless its a collab or have a big goal of course. You probably felt extra exhausted this week because the games you are playing this week are similar to a Minecraft stream, where there are a lot of empty space you had to fill in with your chit chat. You could do your Minecraft stream like that one Minecraft stream you did though, the one with Marshmallow's question, so that you will have topic to talk about whenever you are out of topic.
